Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] General Ibragim Suleymenov, chairman of the Chechen 
National Salvation Committee, has refuted rumors about a peace 
deal between the armed opposition and General Dzhokhar Dudayev's 
regime. He said to the ANI agency that the opposition is not 
going to renounce the use of force, although it would prefer 
avoiding bloodshed. 
  Ibragim Sulelymenov said that the National Salvation 
Committee formations are well armed and have reached agreements 
about joint actions with other armed groups. 

